Sakuzu (assets/libs/sakuzu.js) is an in-house geometric diagram renderer
authored as part of the md-previewer project. It is an ORIGINAL
implementation and does NOT incorporate, derive from, translate, or copy
any code from the GPL-licensed Eukleides tool (https://www.eukleides.org/)
or from the unrelated npm package "euclid.js" (or any other geometry
library).

Mathematical constructions used internally (midpoint, foot of perpendicular,
circle through three points, orthocenter, line/circle intersection, etc.)
are textbook Euclidean geometry and are not subject to copyright. The
implementation, source language design, parser, evaluator, and SVG renderer
were developed independently for this project.

The Japanese name "Sakuzu" (作図) translates to "geometric construction",
which is the classical activity this module supports.

It is distributed under the same license as md-previewer. See the top-level
LICENSE file for the applicable terms.
